Summer classes (May Term, Summer Term 1, Summer Term 1) may be offered online or in person. Please carefully review the section to identify if the course is offered in person or online. Courses with sections of "O" will be offered online for May Term, Summer Term 1, or Summer Term 2, only.

  • Synchronous: If your course is indicated as "synchronous", you will see "SYN" in the "Location" column. For this online format, you will need to be available to be online for class during the days and times indicated.
  • Hybrid: If your course is indicated as "hybrid", you will see "HYB" in the "Location" column. For this online format, your professor will indicate on the syllabus the days you will need to be available for class meetings.
  • Asynchronous: If your course is indicated as "asynchronous", you will see "ASY" in the "Location" column. For this online format, you will not have designated class days and times for the course.
Please note that locations, instructors, and the teaching mode of courses may be subject to change.
